    "In 1936 Penrose organized the first International Surrealist Exhibition in London.": [],
    "The show, which contained many works from Penrose's collection, helped establish understanding of this movement in England.": [],
    "During World War II, he was a lecturer to the Home Guard (1940-42) and a camouflage painter in the army (1943-45).": [],
    "Together with <a href=\"/readh\">Herbert Read</a>, he founded the Institute of Contemporary Arts in 1947.": [],
